vised, an old oath about keeping crossings open that tastes of salt and smoke. Where suction peat breathes under a mat, you spread weight like a lesson across the planks, and in places where the night wants to make you forget the kindness owed, you rehearse names under your breath until memory holds fast like a good knot.\", \"outcome\": \"The convoy ghosts the worst of the Ford’s teeth, bypassing a place where a line of cut cork floats like a trapper’s smile, and the only sounds are the drip of slow water and the soft remorse of boots on wet wood. A snag rises like a remembered mistake but passes beneath without taking more than a thread of hemp, and even the lamp-eels, hungry for light, are starved by your dim discipline. On the far side of the mint-channel, the river’s main throat opens again, and the tones come back clearer for a few long breaths, enough for your prism-lamp to record a pattern that suggests an imposed dissonance rather than a natural one. A shape in the reeds keeps pace for twenty heartbeats and then stops dead, as if a listening post had decided it had heard enough, and Rook swears he saw a flash of beadwork like Kelvar guard-livery on a wrist, which is its own question to carry to Mara. You emerge with every sack and pane intact, no blood fed to the river, and a story that the Covenant can use to chart a safer dusk lane without lighting a fire that others must spend a winter putting out.\"}\n      ],\n      \"connections\": {\"previous\": [], \"next\": [\"M2\"]},\n      \"rewards\": [\n        {\"type\": \"Reputation\", \"description\": \"Pilots’ Covenant reputation (modest increase): word spreads along the piers that you kept rope, grain, and tempers intact while reading the river true.\"},\n        {\"type\": \"Knowledge\", \"description\": \"Updated prism-lamp convoy codes for fog signaling: a refreshed braid of pulses and shutters tailored to the Ford’s current harmonics and dusk-traffic habits.\"},\n        {\"type\": \"Currency\", \"desc